  <static seed="1168" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalFunctions/reduceRationalFunction10.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ f(y) = {\frac{y+7}{y^{2}+10y+21}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>f(y)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{1}{y+3}, y\ne -7</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   f(y) \amp = {\frac{y+7}{y^{2}+10y+21}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{y+7}}{{\left(y+7\right)\mathopen{}\left(y+3\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{1}{y+3}, y\ne -7}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>y+7</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>y \ne -7</m>.</p>
</solution>
